<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/"><channel><title>Imgur Gallery</title><link>https://imgur.com</link><description>description</description><lastBuildDate>2022-06-30 14:11:21.712933</lastBuildDate><item><title>In light of the latest SCOTUS ruling ....</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/1sdiK1N</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/Hjj82mX.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/1sdiK1N</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[blank666man]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Mic drop</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/DuejMiS</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/fk2ACpI.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/DuejMiS</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[kittenpettingfool]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Consequences ....</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/OJH2NyZ</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/AN9Hdte.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/OJH2NyZ</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[blank666man]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Refresh - a comic about burnout</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/siQYVPi</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/jUoOmIM.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/96hdbfk.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/IlBdxkZ.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/lAPitH3.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/UDykAJI.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/SsRIgcP.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>When I started working from home, I was comfy and happy in my jammies, I got to cook my lunch in my own kitchen, and I got to spend all day with my cat. However, I quickly realized I don't hate people as much as I thought I did and started to spin into a depressive state. I changed jobs, traveled a tiny bit, and things got a lot better. Thus, comic inspiration was born! :) Thanks for reading</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/siQYVPi</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[sleepyheadkl]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>A country founded on racism, sexism, and genocide.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/CX7Bo4u</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/mb6QONB.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/tI1FofH.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/CX7Bo4u</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[neoswhiterabbitt]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Living my best life as a medieval peasant</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/pIbz78N</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/ACqWqAP.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I recently visited Evermore Park in Pleasant Grove, Utah. This is a permanent park that is a perfect blend of Renaissance Faire and Live Action Role Play</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/lyzWqqr.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Guests are encouraged to come in character and in costume! My name was Juniper. I just needed something to wear…</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/O89WLrW.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I’ve always wanted to learn to sew and make costumes and used the pandemic to really dive in. Both corsets and skirts were handmade by me!</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/jsgHxjr.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>The green was my first attempt and I’m so proud of it! Not perfect and my skills were definitely more refined by the navy one.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/GfvjVMU.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Evermore park also had a statue in their church graveyard of Saint Apollonia. The patron saint of teeth, which was so perfect for me because I’m a dental hygienist! See her forceps? Guests leave offerings to her for fortune and favor for good teeth.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/vPqa5Ax.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>This park is beautiful. So much love is put into it by the actors. It’s also ridiculously affordable, I would have easily paid triple the price for admission. You interact with characters to go on quests to earn gold and other treasures. One wizard told our fortunes from Pokémon Cards!</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/VhH0thV.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>These are some of my treasures I won in the park. A dragon’s tear from the dragon trainers guild, a special gold doubloon from the pirates, a ruby, a key to the inn so we would always have a place to stay if we came back to Evermore, a ring from the finger of a fairy, and I kept one of the pieces of gold which is just painted rocks. I gave the rest of my gold back to the Evermore actors to recycle to new guests.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/SRBvQnl.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>This is the Pigmyweed’s Inn, if you give the dwarf innkeeper Fergus 3 pieces of gold he will sing you a song. Since I visited the dragon trainers guild (which I joined) got a huge lifelike dragon! And they have baby dragons. There’s also jousts, archery, axe throwing, and more!</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/7E96v8Z.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Stop in their attached restaurant and bar called Vander’s Keep. There I had some of the best venison of my life and amazing cocktails.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/5oq0YVT.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>We were there on Fairy weekend when they had a lantern festival. You can choose to join the guild of fairies, pirates, knights, dragon trainers, and more!</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/9iand2d.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>TLDR - Go LARP in Utah 

FRONT PAGE EDIT: my goodness thank you guys so much! I’ve gotten lots of questions on what patterns I used and how to start sewing. I used Butterick 4669 as a base for the corset bodice. I had to modify it to fit my smaller bust, added the boning channels to give it structure just by eyeballing it, and enclosed the edges with bias tape - that part was all hand sewn because ✨I hate myself✨For the bones themselves I used a classic costumer’s trick of industrial strength zip ties. I taught myself how to sew through lots of YouTube. Rachel Maksy, Morgan Donner, and Bernadette Banner are my favorite sewing/costuming youtubers. No the corset is not uncomfortable and does not make it hard to breathe. It’s well fitted and tailored for me so it fits close but is not stifling. Big poofy sleeves and full skirts give the optical illusion of a small waist. It’s all about the silhouette. 

Happy sewing and costuming!

And for everyone in the comments coming after me for not being “historically accurate” clearly I’m not trying to be. I was riddling with wizards and collecting moss from fairies for gods sake. “Medieval” encompasses a time frame of literally a thousand years (5th to 15th centuries CE) There is no such thing as 100% historical accuracy because we have such little documentation of historical and extant garments. What we do know is that people of all classes and time periods loved colors and patterns. Clearly this is fantasy and fun. Let people enjoy things</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/pIbz78N</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[faelurian]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Lovely.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/2tVized</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/hoyVvYo.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/2tVized</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[BluesFish]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>WTF?</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/q21KPfI</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/kdr4H4I.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Tweet link.https://twitter.com/ChrisMurphyCT/status/1542254795779719169</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/q21KPfI</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Mech0T1]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Not a true catholic</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/dC3PslN</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/dLaKelv.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/dC3PslN</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Devi8tor]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>As an American I cannot blame them at all.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/HE9q3Hw</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/umbOI6m.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"><